23/02/2011
ANKARA, Turkey -- The ruling Justice and Development Party (AKP) party submitted a proposal to parliament Tuesday (February 22nd) setting June 12th as the date for the parliamentary elections.
Lawmakers will vote on it next week and so far, no party has objected to the timetable.
Originally, the elections were supposed to be in July, but were moved up, according to analysts, by the government as a vote of confidence before initiating work on a new constitution.
(Zaman - 23/02/11;
Hurriyet, Sabah - 22/02/11)
